Nov 13 2009 	convenient locationhelpful/friendly staffold-style rooms	Visited here with my partner for a conference for 5 days. The hotel is a remaining classic example of early 20th century urban hotel architecture. Our room had a very small bathroom with shower stall only,18' ceilings,and adequate closet space. Liked:price, location to public transportation,staff/services,historic ambiance of an old S.F. hotel. Disliked: shower head fell off when I adjusted it(fixed it myself),cramped bathroom space,worn hole in bed sheet, old toothpaste cap stuck in sink drain. Had cocktails in restaurant,utilized free wifi and/ pay for internet cafe,enjoyed small hotel museum,door staff attentive(both outside and inside lobby).Hotel secured our luggage for 7 hrs. on our day of departure without a fuss. The hotel is historic without a great deal of modernization or renovation...many like this remain in the northeast but are disappearing as travelers demand more amenities commanding much higher prices.The hotel is lucky to employ our chamber maid--hard worker and friendly.	
