Jul 13 2009 	One of the best deals in San Francisco	So I went with my mom, dad, 2 cousins, 2 sets of aunts/uncles, and 3 grandparents. As u can imagine, a relatively big group. So we went to San Francisco for the 4th of July celebration, and might I add, San Francisco has some sweet fireworks. So more about the hotel, parking is 20 dollars a car per night, with in and out privileges and valet parking. 20 bucks may seem like alot, but parking elsewhere in SF is prolly worse, so actually not a bad deal. The hotel room is relatively, bigger than those motel 8's or whatnot. Its got 2 full size beds i think? Not as big as the queen size but still a decent amount. They have rooms for the elderly, the handicap rooms. And those are convenient for the seniors with even more room and a different bathroom setup, which was quite nice. Its location is decent, but there are no major eating places around it, a few diners across the street thats about it. There is a starbucks under it for all your coffee needs and a pretty good looking restaurant, didn't try it cause it was a little pricey for our tastes, but its there nonetheless. The bathrooms overall were kind of small but its not unbearable, but get the handicap room and its huge (hint hint). It's right off the bart exit so you its easy to get to from out of town of if you're going somewhere like on a business trip and such. There are bus lines just a block or two down, which we used to get down to the docks. It's about a 10 minute bus ride so that's prolly recommended to use if you want to stroll around the bay. It has a story for historic moments in the hotel, as it is an older building but refurbished nicely, for those who want to learn about it. At 7 floors, it is one of the larger hotels in SF, besides those marriotts and others that cost 400 a night, so not a bad deal. There is free wi-fi in there so bring your laptops if you need it! If you need a quick stay in SF, and on a budget so you can't stay in marriotts and stuff, this is the place to go.	
