Dec 4 2007 	Convenient City Hotel	We booked this hotel as the first hotel on a two week trip to California. I had stayed at this hotel on two previous occasions some years ago but my wife had never stayed here. She picked the hotel from the pictures and reviews on the internet. We were not disappointed.The hotel is great for the city being within a 20 minute walk of union square and having a MUNI stop right outside the lobby. The rooms have been re-furbished since my last visit and were adequately decorated but not exceptionally appointed. A little more attention to detail in the bathroom would have paid huge dividends and the walk-in wardrobe was little more than a glorified storage cupboard but the rooms were serviced daily and the beds were super comfortable.The location of the hotel leaves it amidst the usual gathering of destitute individuals but we were never harrassed or tormented and let's face it, every major city on the planet suffers the same. We never tried the restaurant in the hotel but I have every reason to believe the excellent reviews that I have read on the internet.We were received with friendly efficiency and were greated daily with a smile and help at reception.The car parking is extortionate by comparison to similar hotels elsewhere in the country but is typical for San-Francisco. We paid $24 per day but this did ensure that the car was secure and a phone call had the car ready and waiting for us whenever we needed it.On the whole I would recommend this hotel to anyone who wished to stay in a good value hotel convenient to the city centre, public transport and thereby all the attractions of the bay. And as it's only twoo blocks from the 9th street ramp, very easy to get to from the airport. We would use this hotel again.	
