Oct 10 2006 	Clean hotel 4 blocks from shopping	We were taking part in a convention, so our stay was free. It's hard to complain about ANYTHING when your stay is free. I'll try to give an honest account of this hotel.The lobby is beautiful. The ceilings are ornate and very tastefully done. There is a security guard in the lobby, which adds a bit of comfort. There is a Starbucks attached to the lobby, which was wonderful each morning. The staff are helpful and friendly. There is an internet/computer room, and you can purchase minutes to use which is convienent. There is also a gift shop, restuarant and an ATM on this floor. The elevators are quick and easy to catch, not much waiting around for one.Our room had 2 double beds in it. The bedding was very soft and comfortable, except for the bedspread. The pillows are high and soft and we slept very well. The bathroom was clean, but the fixtures were very old. There wasn't much room around the vanity to put items. There was little to no outside noise, and the place is very quiet.It's located on Market Street, just about 4 blocks up from all major shopping. Not a long walk at all, but you will encounter several homeless people and beggars on your way. It was most difficult in the morning, as some of them were in a bad way with the 'shakes'. At no time did I feel unsafe around anyone, however I did feel uncomfortable at times.There is a 'BART' terminal right outside the front door, but we didn't use it, so I can't comment other than 'it's there'. The front desk were so helpful with directions and the like, it was very easy to get around. There are maps and information booklets in the lobby, and you'll have your travel questions answered.We didn't eat at the restaurant, however they did supply us with breakfast each morning, which was just ok. The bacon was so greasy I didn't want to eat it, but the eggs were good.I hope this review helps!!!	
